  "prompt": "What is the toughest question asked in an interview but needed presence of mind to answer it.?",
  "response": "Some of the toughest interview questions that require quick thinking and presence of mind include:\n\n1. \"Tell me about yourself\"\n- Requires concise, strategic self-presentation\n- Need to balance personal and professional details\n- Demonstrate relevance to the job\n\n2. \"Why should we hire you?\"\n- Demands confident, compelling self-promotion\n- Requires instant articulation of unique value proposition\n- Must align skills with company's specific needs\n\n3. \"What is your greatest weakness?\"\n- Needs honest yet strategic response\n- Requires demonstrating self-awareness\n- Should show commitment to improvement\n\n4. \"Where do you see yourself in 5 years?\"\n- Requires forward-thinking perspective\n- Must show ambition without appearing unrealistic\n- Should align with company's growth potential\n\n5. \"Describe a challenging situation and how you handled it\"\n- Needs quick recall of specific professional experience\n- Demonstrate problem-solving skills\n- Show emotional intelligence\n\n6. \"Why are you leaving your current job?\"\n- Demands diplomatic, professional language\n- Avoid negativity\n- Show positive motivation\n\n7. \"What salary are you expecting?\"\n- Requires market research and confidence\n- Balance between self-worth and flexibility\n- Demonstrate understanding of compensation structures\n\nThe key is maintaining composure, being authentic, and providing thoughtful, strategic responses.",
